WEBVTT

00:00.617 --> 00:03.537
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

00:03.538 --> 00:05.821
(SIZZLING)

00:07.000 --> 00:13.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

00:26.430 --> 00:28.181
- All right. Bon appétit.
- Thanks, Chef.

00:28.182 --> 00:29.733
- To the chef.
- To the chef.

00:29.734 --> 00:32.067
Chef, your lawyer's here.

00:32.069 --> 00:34.687
(STEAM HISSING)

00:39.944 --> 00:42.361
(FOLK MUSIC PLAYS)

01:10.891 --> 01:12.843
What? I'm up. What?

01:13.484 --> 01:15.601
Thanks. Thanks, buddy.

01:16.737 --> 01:18.071
(SIGHS)

01:18.072 --> 01:19.189
Oh! Damn it.

01:19.190 --> 01:21.158
Okay. All right.

01:21.159 --> 01:23.692
Oka... No, you go. Go, go.

01:28.282 --> 01:29.249
(SIGHS)

01:29.250 --> 01:30.616
Ooh, that's right.

01:32.336 --> 01:33.870
TOMMY: So, after school,
maybe we'll, uh...

01:33.871 --> 01:36.456
We'll stop by the art store
and get you a new sketchbook

01:36.457 --> 01:38.542
and, um, some of those...

01:38.543 --> 01:39.876
What... what... What were those called?

01:39.877 --> 01:42.761
Charcoal somethings?

01:44.382 --> 01:46.849
Yeah. Worth a shot.

01:51.055 --> 01:52.055
(DOOR BUZZES)

01:52.056 --> 01:55.058
You know, I still had eight months.

01:55.059 --> 01:56.359
You're amazing.

01:56.360 --> 01:57.727
Okay. Just...

01:57.728 --> 02:00.112
I didn't actually do...

02:01.315 --> 02:03.900
With all due respect, I
wish you'd gotten life.

02:03.901 --> 02:05.652
Maybe you'll lose a few pounds, huh?

02:05.653 --> 02:09.572
Hey, go change. I'll
explain your parole terms.

02:20.468 --> 02:22.085
Hey, hey.

02:22.086 --> 02:23.586
Come here.

02:25.423 --> 02:27.340
(SMOOCHES)

02:27.341 --> 02:29.392
All right.

02:29.393 --> 02:31.227
Be good.

02:36.067 --> 02:39.351
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

02:54.285 --> 02:55.669
(SNORTING)

02:55.670 --> 02:56.952
Ahh.

03:01.375 --> 03:03.376
Seriously, I don't
know how you did that,

03:03.377 --> 03:05.595
but thank you.

03:05.596 --> 03:07.964
We should celebrate tonight.

03:07.965 --> 03:10.132
Well, what's wrong with right now?

03:11.769 --> 03:13.435
Come here.

03:26.651 --> 03:28.868
- Hey, Tommy!
- Hey, guys.

03:28.869 --> 03:30.953
- Hey, Tommy!
- What's up, Tommy?

03:36.494 --> 03:38.712
No association with known felons.

03:38.713 --> 03:40.163
No weapons,

03:40.164 --> 03:42.165
and of course (MOANS)

03:42.166 --> 03:44.501
you can't... vote!

03:44.502 --> 03:45.634
(MOANS)

03:53.177 --> 03:55.395
So when am I gonna see you again?

03:55.396 --> 03:58.348
Well, I got to confess, I'm
always getting into trouble.

03:58.349 --> 04:02.184
And when I do, I know where
to find a good lawyer.

04:08.242 --> 04:09.943
(SIGHS)

04:09.944 --> 04:12.195
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

04:12.196 --> 04:13.580
Do you know how hard it is

04:13.581 --> 04:15.749
to get pink peonies this time of year?

04:15.750 --> 04:18.416
Thanks, Jane. They're
my wife's favorite.

04:20.036 --> 04:21.452
(DOOR BUZZES)

04:23.124 --> 04:25.709
- God damn.
- Bye, Chef. Take care, buddy.

04:25.710 --> 04:28.010
It's been a pleasure.

04:33.684 --> 04:35.135
(DOOR BUZZES)

04:35.136 --> 04:36.935
(ENGINE STARTS)

04:44.362 --> 04:46.529
(TIRES SCREECH)

04:46.530 --> 04:48.864
(HORNS BLARING)

04:52.486 --> 04:55.572
(FOLK MUSIC PLAYS)

04:55.573 --> 04:58.040
(TIRES SCREECHING)

05:06.917 --> 05:09.001
What the hell are you doing?!

05:11.005 --> 05:12.972
Hey, I got to be somewhere, pal.

05:12.973 --> 05:14.474
Empty your truck onto the street.

05:14.475 --> 05:16.425
Screw you.

05:19.563 --> 05:22.148
I'd appreciate some civility...

05:22.149 --> 05:23.566
and some cooperation.

05:23.567 --> 05:25.068
So sorry, Mr. Woijchik.

05:25.069 --> 05:26.820
I didn't realize it was you.

05:26.821 --> 05:28.688
How's your father?

05:28.689 --> 05:31.107
Getting by. Now, if you'd please.

05:31.108 --> 05:33.275
Yeah, yeah. Sure thing.

05:47.341 --> 05:49.959
(GLASS SHATTERING)

05:49.960 --> 05:52.262
He's not here, boss.

05:52.263 --> 05:55.297
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

06:12.199 --> 06:13.899
(SNIFFS)

06:22.159 --> 06:25.160
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

06:28.466 --> 06:31.801
♪ Fever dreams ♪

06:31.802 --> 06:34.837
♪ Or so it seems ♪

06:36.223 --> 06:38.224
♪ All I see is ♪

06:38.225 --> 06:41.060
♪ What used to be ♪

06:41.061 --> 06:43.680
♪ Fever dreams ♪

06:43.681 --> 06:47.517
♪ I've been around, I'm lost and found ♪

06:47.518 --> 06:50.904
♪ I burned it all to the ground ♪

06:50.905 --> 06:54.524
♪ Ashes to ashes, hope that dashes ♪

06:54.525 --> 06:58.445
♪ My own new mystery ♪

06:58.446 --> 07:03.532
♪ And all I see is what I used to be ♪

07:04.648 --> 07:07.908
<font color="#ff0000">Sync and corrections by btsix
www.addic7ed.com</font>

07:11.466 --> 07:14.767
(SLOW MUSIC PLAYS)

07:30.555 --> 07:32.673
So, can I put you down
for the usual 10 cases?

07:32.674 --> 07:35.175
Uh, no. Let's go with four this time.

07:40.015 --> 07:42.600
How's your boy doing?

07:42.601 --> 07:46.019
T.J.? Never better.

07:49.441 --> 07:51.526
MAN: T.J...

07:51.527 --> 07:53.694
You don't have to talk, but
you do have to listen.

07:53.695 --> 07:57.165
Now do the assignment.

07:57.166 --> 07:59.533
(BELL RINGING)

08:04.706 --> 08:06.456
What, what?

08:08.510 --> 08:10.094
What are you gonna do about it, punk?

08:10.095 --> 08:11.537
You got something to say?

08:22.608 --> 08:24.192
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

08:24.193 --> 08:25.976
(SPEAKS GREEK)

08:26.728 --> 08:28.362
Uncle Stavros!

08:28.363 --> 08:30.481
Hey, the prodigal nephew. Huh?

08:30.482 --> 08:32.232
(LAUGHS)

08:32.234 --> 08:33.400
Smells like a sewer.

08:33.402 --> 08:34.868
Huh? (SNIFFS)

08:38.991 --> 08:40.907
(CLEAR THROAT)

08:43.078 --> 08:44.712
Passport.

08:44.713 --> 08:46.547
Ticket to Paris.

08:46.548 --> 08:47.832
Spending money.

08:47.833 --> 08:49.300
Flight is at noon tomorrow.

08:49.301 --> 08:51.886
Maury Finkelberg? Really?

08:51.887 --> 08:53.838
Could you have given me any less notice?

08:53.839 --> 08:55.673
You're welcome.

08:55.674 --> 08:57.558
Uncle, reminding you I
need tomorrow night off.

08:57.559 --> 08:58.893
My daughter's talent show.

08:58.894 --> 09:01.846
Consider me reminded, lovely.

09:01.847 --> 09:04.764
Hi, Dion. Bye, Dion.

09:07.603 --> 09:09.103
Can I stay here tonight?

09:09.104 --> 09:10.822
All of my rooms and all
my girls are booked.

09:10.823 --> 09:13.407
I'm telling you, the Bronx
is the next damn Gold Rush.

09:13.408 --> 09:14.775
Which is why these lotto machines

09:14.776 --> 09:16.359
are working overtime.

09:19.031 --> 09:20.364
Son of a bitch.

09:20.365 --> 09:22.166
Come on. Get out.

09:22.167 --> 09:25.168
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

09:27.456 --> 09:29.005
Going already? Huh? (CHUCKLES)

09:31.627 --> 09:34.629
Patrick. It's not your usual time.

09:34.630 --> 09:36.297
I'm looking for your nephew.

09:36.298 --> 09:37.715
Dion?

09:37.716 --> 09:40.718
Doesn't get out for months.

09:40.719 --> 09:42.470
Find him.

09:42.471 --> 09:44.021
You know, there's a
couple of cops up there,

09:44.022 --> 09:45.223
maybe a judge.

09:45.224 --> 09:46.974
That's not good for
business, yours or mine.

09:46.975 --> 09:49.227
What happens to people who lie to me?

09:49.228 --> 09:50.862
Screw you, Patrick!

09:50.863 --> 09:52.947
I pay your dogs every
month for protection.

09:52.948 --> 09:54.982
You call that protection?

09:54.983 --> 09:57.652
You do know why they
call me the Tooth Fairy.

09:57.653 --> 09:59.986
Don't you?

10:01.490 --> 10:03.039
He's not here.

10:15.470 --> 10:18.388
(WINE POURING)

10:29.067 --> 10:30.568
(KNOCKS) Mr. Moran, hi.

10:30.569 --> 10:33.688
You missed last week's appointment.

10:33.689 --> 10:34.772
Yeah, sorry.

10:34.773 --> 10:36.524
Uh, work's... Work's been brutal.

10:36.525 --> 10:38.442
I'll call to set something up.

10:38.443 --> 10:41.579
Well, we have about 15 minutes
till school lets out.

10:41.580 --> 10:43.363
Come on.

10:45.951 --> 10:47.702
My health insurance only covered

10:47.703 --> 10:49.704
10 sessions with a shrink

10:49.705 --> 10:52.186
and 10 sessions with a speech therapist,

10:52.187 --> 10:55.022
but now... now it's maxed
out, and it's all on me.

10:55.023 --> 10:58.860
It's just a lot to juggle
without his mom around.

10:58.861 --> 11:01.362
I can only imagine.

11:01.363 --> 11:04.281
Yeah, you can only imagine.

11:05.534 --> 11:07.869
What are you thinking?

11:07.870 --> 11:10.421
I'm thinking if you had
20 years more experience,

11:10.422 --> 11:12.707
what a difference that
would make for T.J.

11:12.708 --> 11:14.258
You are totally deflecting.

11:14.259 --> 11:17.128
I am who I am. You are who you are.

11:17.129 --> 11:19.547
So let's... Let's talk
about what's real...

11:19.548 --> 11:23.217
T.J. failing, T.J. getting into fights,

11:23.218 --> 11:25.470
T.J. not talking. I get it.

11:25.471 --> 11:27.438
You have a lot on your
plate as the only parent.

11:27.439 --> 11:28.639
So what, now, I'm... I'm the only

11:28.640 --> 11:30.641
single parent whose kid is
having trouble in school?

11:30.642 --> 11:32.110
No. You're the only single parent

11:32.111 --> 11:33.978
whose son witnessed his
own mother get killed

11:33.979 --> 11:36.230
in a hit-and-run and
hasn't said a word since.

11:36.231 --> 11:38.733
(BELL RINGS)

11:38.734 --> 11:42.453
And whose father has a drinking problem.

11:42.454 --> 11:44.071
I smell alcohol on your breath.

11:44.072 --> 11:45.373
That's wine.

11:45.374 --> 11:47.208
- I'm a wine rep. That's part...
- Yeah, Mr. Moran,

11:47.209 --> 11:49.293
if this continues to go downhill,

11:49.294 --> 11:52.580
I'm required by law to notify
Child Protective Services.

11:52.581 --> 11:55.133
What does that mean, exactly?

11:55.134 --> 11:56.967
You could lose T.J.

12:08.514 --> 12:11.046
I'm not gonna let anyone take you away.

12:21.160 --> 12:23.109
(DOOR BUZZES)

12:28.834 --> 12:30.117
In trouble so soon?

12:30.118 --> 12:31.586
I miss you already.

12:31.587 --> 12:32.787
(CHUCKLES)

12:32.788 --> 12:34.455
Hey, uh, can I come in?

12:34.456 --> 12:36.757
Ooh. (CHUCKLES)

12:36.758 --> 12:40.545
Look, you're a great lay, but
I think we should keep this

12:40.546 --> 12:43.930
client-attorney business
strictly professional.

12:46.635 --> 12:48.052
(LOCK CLICKS)

12:48.053 --> 12:49.936
(CHUCKLES)

13:07.823 --> 13:10.290
(HORN HONKS)

13:35.317 --> 13:37.068
Good behavior?

13:37.069 --> 13:39.403
Oh, I don't know.

13:39.404 --> 13:41.821
My money's on, uh, good cooking.

13:44.192 --> 13:46.409
(LAUGHS)

13:48.363 --> 13:50.163
- Glad to see you.
- You, too.

13:52.584 --> 13:54.869
Are you gonna crash here?

13:54.870 --> 13:56.704
Yeah.

13:56.705 --> 13:58.456
Yeah, just for one night.

13:58.457 --> 14:01.342
Got to go to Paris tomorrow.

14:01.343 --> 14:03.377
Yeah, I... I got to get away.

14:03.378 --> 14:04.629
That's too bad.

14:04.630 --> 14:06.264
It'd be nice to have you around.

14:06.265 --> 14:07.932
Yeah, I'll be back.

14:07.933 --> 14:10.885
So you were in the one prison
without a weight room?

14:10.886 --> 14:12.436
(CHUCKLES)

14:12.437 --> 14:13.554
Nice.

14:13.555 --> 14:15.939
Don't worry, I'll still kick your ass.

14:18.944 --> 14:20.860
How you doing, man? You okay?

14:23.148 --> 14:25.782
T.J., you remember Dion.

14:27.869 --> 14:32.238
Look at you. Huh? What's up, T-Bone?

14:40.582 --> 14:42.999
All right. Come on.

14:44.636 --> 14:46.670
All right.

14:54.821 --> 14:56.572
Oh, you see they turned
the methadone clinic

14:56.573 --> 14:57.740
into a yoga studio?

14:57.741 --> 15:00.293
Yeah. Got an organic
market coming in, too.

15:00.294 --> 15:01.822
I know. It's crazy, right?

15:01.823 --> 15:03.571
It's like I said, you know,

15:03.572 --> 15:05.907
the Bronx is the new Brooklyn.

15:05.908 --> 15:09.243
Eh, it's coming up, man.

15:09.244 --> 15:10.995
Yeah, well, parts of it.

15:10.996 --> 15:13.130
Maid called in sick.

15:15.084 --> 15:17.335
Look, how do you live like this, huh?

15:17.336 --> 15:19.470
I had better things back in prison.

15:19.471 --> 15:23.424
Well, I'm sure they'd
make room for you again.

15:23.425 --> 15:27.228
Hey, uh, is T.J. all right? You
know, he seems a little...

15:27.229 --> 15:28.262
Quiet?

15:28.263 --> 15:29.430
Dented.

15:29.431 --> 15:32.567
Dented, I'll take. It's
broken I'm worried about.

15:32.568 --> 15:34.268
He hasn't spoken since she died.

15:34.269 --> 15:37.822
Oh, thanks for coming to
the funeral, by the way.

15:37.823 --> 15:39.240
(CHUCKLES)

15:39.241 --> 15:41.109
Oh, yeah, well, uh, the county jail

15:41.110 --> 15:42.994
was all out of hall passes that day.

15:42.995 --> 15:45.279
Oh, Tommy, Tommy, Tommy, Tommy,
Tommy, you're killing me.

15:45.280 --> 15:48.616
You... You got a $20,000 stove,
and your fridge is empty.

15:48.617 --> 15:51.619
Well, there's not a lot of
time for grocery shopping.

15:51.620 --> 15:54.622
All stocked up on wine,
though, I see, huh?

15:54.623 --> 15:56.958
How are you and the bottle
getting along these days?

15:56.959 --> 15:58.292
Really well, actually.

15:58.293 --> 16:00.011
Yeah? Yeah, no. We're... We're in love.

16:00.012 --> 16:01.179
How about you and the blow?

16:01.180 --> 16:02.847
We broke up.

16:02.848 --> 16:05.516
'Cause it's so hard to
get drugs in prison.

16:05.517 --> 16:07.852
Yeah.

16:07.853 --> 16:10.021
Yeah, thanks for coming
to visit me, by the way.

16:10.022 --> 16:12.273
I'm sorry. Was I not there for you?

16:12.274 --> 16:15.143
That's funny, uh, 'cause
the way I remember it,

16:15.144 --> 16:17.311
the one time I really needed you,

16:17.312 --> 16:19.230
you know, when my wife was killed,

16:19.231 --> 16:22.316
you got coked up and burned down
the restaurant we worked at.

16:22.317 --> 16:24.285
So not only did I lose my wife,

16:24.286 --> 16:26.320
I lost my best friend and my job.

16:26.321 --> 16:28.872
So no, no, thank you.

16:31.660 --> 16:33.660
I'm sorry about Rie.

16:34.496 --> 16:37.131
I miss her, too, you know?

16:37.132 --> 16:39.584
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

16:39.585 --> 16:42.303
Hey, what's up, T-bone?

16:42.304 --> 16:43.721
You hungry?

16:43.722 --> 16:46.339
(FOLK MUSIC PLAYS)

17:13.702 --> 17:16.036
So, put it down like that.

17:19.340 --> 17:21.508
(SIZZLING)

17:34.223 --> 17:37.158
Ah, j-j-just... Just hold on, champ.

17:39.221 --> 17:40.972
What?

17:40.973 --> 17:42.474
Go on.

17:42.475 --> 17:43.808
Oh, come on, man.

17:43.809 --> 17:45.527
Tommy, what are you doing?
The food's getting cold.

17:45.528 --> 17:46.728
Uh, look, I'm really...

17:46.729 --> 17:47.946
I'm really not having this with you.

17:47.947 --> 17:50.648
All right, listen, the kid doesn't eat

17:50.649 --> 17:52.649
until you do it.

17:57.873 --> 18:01.743
Tonight, we have, uh, our special...

18:01.744 --> 18:05.213
House-made malfatti with
vine-ripened Roma tomatoes,

18:05.214 --> 18:06.965
Parmesan, and basil.

18:06.966 --> 18:12.170
Pairs perfectly with this
2010 Chianti Classico,

18:12.171 --> 18:17.308
an old-world Sangiovese,
aged in traditional botti.

18:17.309 --> 18:21.513
That's large-format
barrels, neutral oak.

18:21.514 --> 18:25.984
Look for dried red
fruits, a medium body,

18:25.985 --> 18:30.404
and a bright, mouthwatering acidity.

18:32.691 --> 18:33.691
And he's back.

18:33.692 --> 18:34.859
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

18:34.860 --> 18:36.694
Can we eat already?

18:36.695 --> 18:38.746
(SNIFFS)

18:40.750 --> 18:43.751
(TRAIN SQUEALING)

18:53.012 --> 18:55.547
Okay, so I'm a little out of
practice cooking Italian.

18:55.548 --> 18:56.714
What do you mean?

18:56.715 --> 18:58.433
That meal was perfectly mediocre.

18:58.434 --> 18:59.767
(CHUCKLES)

19:06.058 --> 19:07.809
I still want to do Greek.

19:07.810 --> 19:10.895
Yeah, well, it's gonna be hard
if you're moving to Paris.

19:10.896 --> 19:13.114
Oh, why don't you come to Paris with me?

19:13.115 --> 19:14.065
(CHUCKLES)

19:14.066 --> 19:16.200
Seriously.

19:17.036 --> 19:19.070
We could do the restaurant there.

19:19.071 --> 19:20.572
Great idea.

19:20.573 --> 19:22.407
Yeah, T.J.'s old enough
to live here on his own.

19:22.408 --> 19:23.792
Oh, no, no. T.J.'s already coming.

19:23.793 --> 19:25.376
We... We just wanted to
know if you wanted to come.

19:25.377 --> 19:27.579
Oh, yeah? (LAUGHS)

19:27.580 --> 19:29.914
You're out of your mind.

19:29.915 --> 19:33.501
Seriously, though. I
mean, think about it.

19:33.502 --> 19:35.303
You know, you, me, Teej...

19:35.304 --> 19:38.890
Three bachelors letting
loose in the city of love.

19:38.891 --> 19:42.393
Come on, man, we... we would
have the best Greek restaurant

19:42.394 --> 19:44.762
in all of Paris.

19:44.763 --> 19:47.232
I can't uproot T.J. like that.

19:47.233 --> 19:48.899
He's been through enough change.

19:50.769 --> 19:53.404
Seems he needs a fresh start
almost as much as you do.

19:53.405 --> 19:55.323
It's not that simple.

19:55.324 --> 19:57.942
Besides, I-I-I can't handle that
whole French scene without you.

19:57.943 --> 20:00.695
Who's gonna make fun of it with me? Huh?

20:00.696 --> 20:02.947
Come on, seriously. I-I-I won't survive.

20:02.948 --> 20:05.582
You always survive.

20:07.620 --> 20:10.003
(CHUCKLES)

20:13.792 --> 20:16.344
All right.

20:16.345 --> 20:18.129
All right, look at that.

20:18.130 --> 20:20.131
Tell me... What do you see?

20:20.132 --> 20:21.766
Uh, a plate?

20:21.767 --> 20:23.468
No.

20:23.469 --> 20:26.187
You see black orzo

20:26.188 --> 20:29.190
in a spicy seafood broth

20:29.191 --> 20:31.309
and a celeriac puree.

20:31.310 --> 20:33.027
(SNIFFS)

20:33.028 --> 20:37.482
Topped with, uh, grilled octopus

20:37.483 --> 20:40.368
and slow-roasted cherry tomatoes,

20:40.369 --> 20:45.907
perfectly finished with
micro bronzed fennel.

20:45.908 --> 20:47.909
Mmm!

20:47.910 --> 20:50.828
Classic Mediterranean,
with a very specific

20:50.829 --> 20:54.132
and dare I say very personal
Hellenic influence.

20:54.133 --> 20:56.301
Dude, I helped you come
up with this whole menu.

20:56.302 --> 20:57.918
You don't have to walk me through it.

20:59.421 --> 21:01.422
You know, uh, in prison,

21:01.423 --> 21:04.008
all anyone's ever thinking
about is escaping.

21:04.009 --> 21:06.477
You know what I was thinking about?

21:06.478 --> 21:08.229
I was thinking about Thirio.

21:08.230 --> 21:10.481
Who do you think you're talking to?

21:10.482 --> 21:14.185
Downstairs, all I see are
Rie's unfinished designs.

21:14.186 --> 21:16.321
That giant espresso machine from Italy,

21:16.322 --> 21:18.489
Rie put that together herself.

21:18.490 --> 21:21.109
I look up to the ceiling, I see...
I see pine beams.

21:21.110 --> 21:22.193
Cypress.

21:22.194 --> 21:23.361
The whole... What?

21:23.362 --> 21:24.862
Cypress beams.

21:24.863 --> 21:26.698
It's a Mediterranean restaurant.

21:26.699 --> 21:28.999
There is no pine in the Mediterranean.

21:30.536 --> 21:32.086
I'm pretty sure it's pine.

21:32.087 --> 21:33.954
Well, where's the "Bible"? Forget it.

21:35.708 --> 21:37.424
Come on, take a look.

21:43.933 --> 21:45.550
Wow.

21:45.551 --> 21:48.353
It was a long time ago.

21:48.354 --> 21:50.438
It was a lifetime ago.

21:50.439 --> 21:52.473
Yeah.

21:52.474 --> 21:54.107
Wow.

22:00.199 --> 22:02.367
Uh-oh. Boom.

22:02.368 --> 22:03.735
Bite me.

22:03.736 --> 22:06.204
Come on, imagine it.

22:06.205 --> 22:08.239
Thirio in Paris.

22:08.240 --> 22:10.958
With the two of us, man, we
could totally pull it off.

22:12.911 --> 22:17.632
It was the three of us that
were gonna pull it off.

22:17.633 --> 22:19.883
I could never do it any other way.

22:22.946 --> 22:25.648
First, the Chinks come in.

22:25.649 --> 22:29.369
Then the Mighty Irish push them out,

22:29.370 --> 22:31.487
until the Wops and the Jews take over.

22:31.488 --> 22:37.327
And, then, whoops, here come
the Coloreds and the Spics

22:37.328 --> 22:40.330
and... bam... now the
Vietnamese or Cambodians,

22:40.331 --> 22:42.465
whatever the hell they are.

22:42.466 --> 22:44.500
So basically, it's Chink to Chink,

22:44.501 --> 22:47.170
circle of life.

22:47.171 --> 22:49.339
My father, rest his soul,

22:49.340 --> 22:51.724
used to say a neighborhood
is like an organism,

22:51.725 --> 22:55.511
a living thing, always changing,
always needing something.

22:55.512 --> 22:59.682
And a good businessman finds out
what that need is and fills it.

22:59.683 --> 23:04.520
No offense to my old man,
but what he didn't know...

23:04.521 --> 23:06.906
The real money is in filling that need

23:06.907 --> 23:08.991
even when it don't need filling.

23:12.529 --> 23:15.030
Ah, come on.

23:26.043 --> 23:28.210
(GRUNTS)

23:36.770 --> 23:39.188
(WATER FIZZES)

23:39.189 --> 23:41.723
(SIGHS)

23:44.979 --> 23:47.112
(SNIFFS, SIGHS)

23:48.198 --> 23:50.148
(SNORTING)

23:53.070 --> 23:55.487
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

24:01.662 --> 24:03.462
All right, buddy.

24:06.917 --> 24:09.135
Hey, I'm taking Teej to school.

24:09.136 --> 24:11.921
You can stay until your flight, I guess.

24:11.922 --> 24:13.423
Just don't burn the place down.

24:13.424 --> 24:15.091
(CHUCKLES)

24:15.092 --> 24:16.426
Yeah, well, take care, man.

24:16.427 --> 24:18.094
Yep. You too.

24:18.095 --> 24:19.762
Hey, thanks.

24:19.763 --> 24:22.482
And you...

24:22.483 --> 24:24.933
You might want to keep it
down a little bit, huh?

24:27.104 --> 24:29.321
All right.

24:32.693 --> 24:34.609
(SIGHS)

24:37.531 --> 24:39.448
(SNIFFS)

24:45.289 --> 24:48.290
♪

24:58.969 --> 25:01.136
(BELL DINGS)

25:06.894 --> 25:09.528
(MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

25:10.948 --> 25:12.482
DION: Table 33.

25:12.483 --> 25:15.367
All right, let's go. Come on, let's go.

25:18.072 --> 25:21.323
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYS)

25:56.994 --> 25:59.995
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

26:08.205 --> 26:09.872
Is this the grief group?

26:09.873 --> 26:11.090
Yeah.

26:11.091 --> 26:13.459
I'm... I'm Tommy Moran. Welcome.

26:13.460 --> 26:14.961
Thanks.

26:14.962 --> 26:16.546
It's my first time.

26:16.547 --> 26:18.347
It's a little overwhelming.

26:18.348 --> 26:20.132
I remember.

26:22.386 --> 26:25.221
I'm Pilar Herrera.

26:25.222 --> 26:30.359
My husband, Oscar, died in my arms...

26:30.360 --> 26:33.446
of a heart attack.

26:33.447 --> 26:34.981
You?

26:34.982 --> 26:37.784
My wife, Rie, car accident.

26:37.785 --> 26:39.368
I'm sorry.

26:39.369 --> 26:42.872
Me too you.

26:42.873 --> 26:45.540
So, um, what do you do?

26:46.743 --> 26:49.745
One day at a time, I guess.

26:49.746 --> 26:52.215
I meant for a living. (CHUCKLES)

26:52.216 --> 26:54.467
Oh, I'm a sommelier,

26:54.468 --> 26:59.388
but I'm between restaurants,
so, uh, I rep wines.

26:59.389 --> 27:02.308
No way. I'm in the
restaurant business, too.

27:02.309 --> 27:06.929
My sister has a place, La
Cubana Loca, in Harlem.

27:06.930 --> 27:09.732
Actually, I'm, like, the manager.

27:09.733 --> 27:12.602
We're always looking for wines.

27:12.603 --> 27:15.321
We should exchange numbers.

27:15.322 --> 27:18.324
I kept looking at the door,

27:18.325 --> 27:23.329
thinking Rie was gonna
walk in at any second,

27:23.330 --> 27:26.165
but she never did.

27:26.166 --> 27:27.950
She never will.

27:27.951 --> 27:30.920
All right, let's... we're gonna
try a little role-play, okay?

27:30.921 --> 27:34.590
I want you to tell your wife
what it is you're going through.

27:34.591 --> 27:36.626
Gloria, you... You be his wife, okay?

27:36.627 --> 27:39.545
- (SOBBING) No.
- All right, um, uh...

27:39.546 --> 27:41.464
Pilar, is it? Pilar?

27:41.465 --> 27:43.933
Y-You... Can you do that?
Will that be okay?

27:43.934 --> 27:48.186
So, Tommy, tell Pilar
how you're feeling.

27:52.192 --> 27:54.192
It's okay.

28:00.150 --> 28:02.784
(VOICE BREAKING) I miss you...

28:07.491 --> 28:09.457
all day long.

28:10.494 --> 28:13.161
We were supposed to do this together...

28:15.082 --> 28:17.466
Raise our son, start a restaurant.

28:17.467 --> 28:19.167
I can't...

28:21.305 --> 28:23.172
I need you.

28:23.173 --> 28:25.808
We need you.

28:25.809 --> 28:28.560
(FOLK MUSIC PLAYS)

28:32.015 --> 28:34.649
You're like a phantom limb.

28:38.438 --> 28:40.355
I love you.

28:46.863 --> 28:50.115
♪

29:01.374 --> 29:02.623
Dion.

29:11.503 --> 29:14.172
(SIREN WAILING)

29:16.032 --> 29:17.891
What? What the...

29:29.413 --> 29:30.963
Mm.

29:33.018 --> 29:34.793
Ah, travel.

29:35.330 --> 29:37.863
So good for the soul.

29:40.084 --> 29:42.868
(SIGHS)

29:45.784 --> 29:47.383
Maury Finkelberg?

29:48.420 --> 29:49.869
Short notice.

29:50.622 --> 29:52.050
Not only...

29:53.208 --> 29:57.495
do you burn down our restaurant...

29:58.930 --> 30:00.861
you get caught.

30:04.436 --> 30:06.136
An employee of ours committing arson,

30:06.137 --> 30:08.055
so no insurance.

30:08.056 --> 30:10.050
My father might be in prison.

30:12.477 --> 30:15.396
That doesn't change the fact
that you owe us 600 grand.

30:15.397 --> 30:17.448
- Look, I'm gonna pay it back.
- From Paris?

30:17.449 --> 30:19.566
I'm going on a...

30:19.567 --> 30:23.404
<i>Was</i> going on a... On a sourcing trip.

30:23.405 --> 30:27.157
My new restaurant needs
top-of-the-line equipment.

30:27.158 --> 30:29.959
Dion, Dion, Dion.

30:33.081 --> 30:36.083
Come and take a look. I'll show you.

30:36.084 --> 30:39.085
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYS)

30:44.476 --> 30:46.593
Obviously, we're still, uh, you know,

30:46.594 --> 30:49.480
in the process of setting up,
but, you know, we got...

30:49.481 --> 30:52.766
Got a Jade freestanding range over here,

30:52.767 --> 30:54.902
the Belle Epoque,

30:54.903 --> 30:56.770
brass and copper espresso machine

30:56.771 --> 30:59.440
we had specially shipped in from Italy.

30:59.441 --> 31:01.275
We have a, uh... A walk-in fridge

31:01.276 --> 31:02.693
that's gonna go over there.

31:02.694 --> 31:05.112
Now, the prep and, uh,
cooking stations are...

31:05.113 --> 31:08.832
They're gonna go here, here, there.

31:08.833 --> 31:10.617
Yeah, we're, uh... We're looking into...

31:10.618 --> 31:12.919
To cypress pillars for the dining room.

31:15.006 --> 31:17.458
Plus, uh, we're gonna be
growing our own herbs

31:17.459 --> 31:19.460
in the greenhouse we're
gonna build up on the roof.

31:19.461 --> 31:23.097
I mean, we could be up and
running within, uh...

31:23.098 --> 31:24.848
Within two months.

31:24.849 --> 31:27.101
Well, you know me and kitchens.

31:27.102 --> 31:29.636
When you're not burning them down.

31:29.637 --> 31:32.355
Yeah. That never gets old.

31:34.726 --> 31:37.945
You were the one who made me
executive chef at Ottavio's.

31:37.946 --> 31:39.146
The profit we were making there,

31:39.147 --> 31:40.647
I can double that.

31:40.648 --> 31:42.149
I can pay you back.

31:42.150 --> 31:48.288
You could be eating braised lamb
with a wild-mushroom ragout

31:48.289 --> 31:51.741
while this place becomes a
laundromat for your money.

31:54.546 --> 31:56.829
People are gonna come.

32:00.135 --> 32:02.168
Okay.

32:03.338 --> 32:07.757
But you try and skip town
again, these two will die.

32:09.094 --> 32:11.228
So will your favorite and only uncle.

32:11.229 --> 32:15.099
Oh, and that lady
lawyer friend of yours.

32:15.100 --> 32:18.936
But you, Dion... I'll let you live

32:18.937 --> 32:22.189
so you'll always remember
what you caused.

32:22.190 --> 32:24.324
Look, uh, I'm not going anywhere.

32:24.325 --> 32:27.360
Good, 'cause I'll be collecting
on your debt every week.

32:30.415 --> 32:32.832
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

32:34.786 --> 32:36.870
I hope this restaurant's a success.

32:36.871 --> 32:38.505
Be a shame if I went
through all the effort

32:38.506 --> 32:39.840
of getting you out of prison early

32:39.841 --> 32:44.427
just to kill everyone who
means something to you.

32:53.271 --> 32:54.721
Come on! What are you doing? No, no!

32:54.722 --> 32:56.974
What are you doing?! Come
on, I can pay you back!

32:56.975 --> 32:58.642
Smile. I'll pay you back!

32:58.643 --> 33:00.861
It will make it so much
easier for the both of us.

33:00.862 --> 33:02.112
Please, Patrick!

33:02.113 --> 33:05.115
(SCREAMING) No! Please,
not the teeth, no!

33:05.116 --> 33:06.366
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

33:06.367 --> 33:08.235
Maybe we try something different?

33:08.236 --> 33:10.070
Oh, God. Oh, God.

33:10.071 --> 33:11.989
Say, a little finger?

33:11.990 --> 33:13.874
No, no! No!

33:13.875 --> 33:16.410
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no!

33:16.411 --> 33:18.495
Oh, God, no!

33:18.496 --> 33:21.665
(SCREAMING) Oh, God!

33:21.666 --> 33:24.217
(GROANING)

33:25.970 --> 33:27.805
See you soon, Dion.

33:27.806 --> 33:30.090
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

33:30.091 --> 33:33.009
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

33:40.602 --> 33:43.986
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

34:06.845 --> 34:10.464
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

34:10.465 --> 34:13.549
Yo. Yo, yo, Manny. Manny.

34:14.886 --> 34:17.436
I need you to do me a solid.

34:33.871 --> 34:35.485
Thanks, bro.

34:46.551 --> 34:48.634
Shouldn't you be halfway
to Paris by now?

34:52.724 --> 34:54.891
What is that? What are you doing?

34:54.893 --> 34:57.343
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:04.519 --> 35:06.352
What happened to your finger?

35:08.239 --> 35:10.357
Uh, cab door.

35:10.358 --> 35:12.192
Is that why you're not in Paris...

35:12.193 --> 35:14.193
'cause... 'cause of your boo-boo?

35:15.280 --> 35:17.197
No.

35:17.198 --> 35:18.915
No.

35:21.452 --> 35:23.086
This is why.

35:23.087 --> 35:26.205
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

35:29.177 --> 35:32.211
(SIZZLING)

36:05.129 --> 36:06.913
All right. Go... Go ahead.

36:06.914 --> 36:08.799
Hold on. I-I have to get some A.1.

36:08.800 --> 36:10.883
If you don't mind, go ahead.

36:22.597 --> 36:25.231
Words would be nice.

36:26.901 --> 36:28.769
It's astonishing,

36:28.770 --> 36:30.270
maybe even perfect.

36:30.271 --> 36:31.605
No, no, no. It's never perfect.

36:31.606 --> 36:34.408
Dude, just take the compliment.
Go ahead, try. Try some.

36:34.409 --> 36:36.242
Come on, try it.

36:38.279 --> 36:39.413
It's good, right?

36:39.414 --> 36:40.614
Now, this...

36:40.615 --> 36:45.369
This is gonna be the
signature dish of Thirio.

36:45.370 --> 36:47.454
Look, I didn't go to
Paris 'cause our dream

36:47.455 --> 36:49.506
was to open a restaurant
right here, man.

36:49.507 --> 36:51.354
We are so doing this!

36:53.262 --> 36:54.544
You got any homework?

36:54.545 --> 36:57.797
All right. Now is a good time.

37:03.938 --> 37:06.390
I told you, I'm not doing
a restaurant without Rie.

37:06.391 --> 37:09.026
If you could see yourself right
now, living in this place.

37:09.027 --> 37:10.977
I'm the one who's been in
prison this last year,

37:10.978 --> 37:12.279
and you're the one who's messed up.

37:12.280 --> 37:14.314
I mean, y-you're stuck, man, bad.

37:14.315 --> 37:16.783
You drink too much. You
work a demeaning job.

37:16.784 --> 37:18.318
It's been almost a year since Rie died.

37:18.319 --> 37:20.153
And what? Come on, what?
You're still wallowing?

37:20.154 --> 37:22.989
Right, right! "Get on with it, Tommy!

37:22.990 --> 37:25.959
Shake it off, Tommy.
Move on, Tommy," right?

37:25.960 --> 37:27.327
All right, look, I'm not saying...

37:27.328 --> 37:30.580
You have no idea what
you're talking about.

37:30.581 --> 37:33.074
You don't know what it's
like to be in love,

37:33.835 --> 37:35.311
to be married,

37:35.837 --> 37:39.339
to raise a son with...
With the woman you love.

37:39.340 --> 37:42.347
And you have no idea what
it's like to lose her.

37:44.345 --> 37:47.013
Man, I had to clean out her closet,

37:47.014 --> 37:49.349
clean out her bathroom,

37:49.350 --> 37:52.435
throw her mouth guard in the trash.

37:53.905 --> 37:55.822
Do not tell me how to grieve,

37:55.823 --> 37:59.658
and don't tell me to open
a restaurant without her.

38:02.530 --> 38:04.447
We're not doing it without her.

38:06.367 --> 38:07.867
We're doing it with her.

38:10.037 --> 38:13.873
She will live through this restaurant.

38:15.676 --> 38:17.034
No, she won't.

38:27.065 --> 38:29.603
♪

38:32.005 --> 38:33.956
I love you more than
anything in the world.

38:34.464 --> 38:36.130
You know that, right?

38:39.052 --> 38:40.853
All right.

38:40.854 --> 38:41.854
(SMOOCHES)

38:41.855 --> 38:44.940
Sweet dreams. See you in the morning.

38:44.941 --> 38:46.308
(METAL CLANGING)

38:46.309 --> 38:48.310
DION: (SCREAMS) Stay in bed.

38:48.311 --> 38:51.897
(GRUNTING)

38:51.898 --> 38:54.365
(SHOUTS)

38:55.694 --> 38:57.278
Hey!

38:57.279 --> 38:58.696
What the hell are you doing?!

38:58.697 --> 38:59.747
Look, if you're not
gonna do a restaurant,

38:59.748 --> 39:00.865
then you don't deserve this!

39:00.866 --> 39:01.916
- Hey, let go.
- Give it back.

39:01.917 --> 39:03.501
- Let go!
- Get your hands off it!

39:03.502 --> 39:05.036
- Hey, hey, hey!
- You're not worthy of it.

39:05.037 --> 39:06.671
You're not worthy!

39:06.672 --> 39:07.956
Get off, get off!

39:07.957 --> 39:09.207
(CLATTERING)

39:09.208 --> 39:10.925
You know what?! You don't
deserve any of this!

39:10.926 --> 39:12.093
Oh. (PLATE SHATTERS)

39:12.094 --> 39:14.596
- Oh, oh! Throwing plates!
- No, none of this!

39:14.597 --> 39:16.097
You must be Greek.

39:16.098 --> 39:17.265
All right, would you stop?!

39:17.266 --> 39:19.049
Hey! Stop! Hey!

39:21.053 --> 39:22.937
You want this just as much as I do.

39:22.938 --> 39:24.389
You're just too much of
a drunk to realize it!

39:24.390 --> 39:26.391
(LAUGHS) The coke head speaks.

39:26.392 --> 39:28.393
This is so you.

39:28.394 --> 39:29.694
I let you crash here,

39:29.695 --> 39:31.479
within 24 hours, you're
trashing the place.

39:31.480 --> 39:33.731
Oh, trashing the place?
What, this shit hole?

39:33.732 --> 39:35.033
What are you even doing here?! Just go!

39:35.034 --> 39:37.235
Oh, I'm so sorry!

39:37.236 --> 39:38.953
Get out. Go on.

39:38.954 --> 39:40.955
Take your massive ego with you...

39:40.956 --> 39:42.740
Oh, I'm sorry to interrupt
your downward spiral,

39:42.741 --> 39:45.326
- you self-loathing, self-pitying...
- you selfish, narcissistic...

39:45.327 --> 39:46.578
shell of your former self!

39:46.579 --> 39:48.912
Selfish son of a... (CELLPHONE RINGING)

39:58.641 --> 40:01.308
(CELLPHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

40:04.184 --> 40:07.302
He's calling to hear Rie's
voice on the outgoing message.

40:11.441 --> 40:13.370
Yeah, well, he's not doing so good, T.

40:13.371 --> 40:14.397
Tell me about it.

40:16.006 --> 40:19.041
Yeah, well, then why do you
make him live like this?

40:19.042 --> 40:21.460
This place, the way
it is, it's like a...

40:21.461 --> 40:25.381
Like a tomb of Rie's dream
that can never come true.

40:25.382 --> 40:28.684
The way I see it, you either
burn it down or you build it up!

40:28.685 --> 40:30.269
Oh, man, y-you got to stop.

40:30.270 --> 40:32.438
No, I don't.

40:32.439 --> 40:33.889
Look, when we were doing the restaurant,

40:33.890 --> 40:35.691
when we were coming up
with plans for Thirio,

40:35.692 --> 40:37.026
you were so amped, man.

40:37.027 --> 40:38.060
You were so alive.

40:38.061 --> 40:39.228
Yeah, I also had a wife.

40:39.229 --> 40:40.563
This isn't about you! Wake up!

40:40.564 --> 40:42.480
This is about your son!

40:44.067 --> 40:46.485
Look, if we do this restaurant

40:46.486 --> 40:48.704
and you get that fire
back in your belly,

40:48.705 --> 40:52.241
you have a purpose again.

40:52.242 --> 40:55.794
And you know how quickly
T.J.'s gonna turn around.

40:57.714 --> 40:58.748
He lost his mom.

40:58.749 --> 41:01.249
He doesn't need to lose his dad, too.

41:03.336 --> 41:05.471
(SCOFFS) We're broke.

41:05.472 --> 41:06.755
Where would we even get the money?

41:10.427 --> 41:12.895
What? No. No way.

41:12.896 --> 41:14.096
No way.

41:14.097 --> 41:16.981
It's the only way. Tommy, he owes you.

41:19.603 --> 41:22.988
I haven't talked to him in 10 years.

41:22.989 --> 41:26.274
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYS)

41:50.133 --> 41:53.351
(SIREN WAILING)

42:06.399 --> 42:09.200
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

42:09.820 --> 42:12.821
(NEON SIGN BUZZING)

42:17.994 --> 42:21.162
♪

42:31.594 --> 42:33.512
You burned down a restaurant

42:33.513 --> 42:36.148
owned by Ziggy Woijchik
and his psycho son,

42:36.149 --> 42:39.017
and you not only live, but
you get out of prison early?

42:39.018 --> 42:41.570
You must be in really tight
with those scumbags.

42:41.571 --> 42:44.022
Eh, you don't know what
you're talking about.

42:44.023 --> 42:46.657
(GROANING)

